-- 
Canada Wage Settlements Averaged 1.9% Annual Increase in August

-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 
2011-10-17T18:55:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/canada-wage-settlements-averaged-1-9-annual-increase-in-august.html
Canadian wage settlements in August
had increases averaging 1.9 percent annually, up from a pace of
1.7 percent in July, according to government figures.  The results are based on a review of 12 major agreements
with 16,730 employees, Human Resources and Skills Development
Canada said in a statement on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Greg Quinn in Ottawa at 
 gquinn1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Badertscher at 
 pbadertscher@bloomberg.net  